snippet: The president of La Liga, Javier Tebas, said Catalan clubs such as Barcelona would be excluded from league soccer should the region succeed in its push for independence from Spain.
abstract: La Liga president Javier Tebas says Catalan clubs like Barcelona would be excluded from league soccer should the region succeed in its push for independence from Spain; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: The president of La Liga, Javier Tebas, said Catalan clubs such as Barcelona would be excluded from league soccer should the region succeed in its push for independence from Spain.

headline.main: Catalan Independence Would Come With a Price for Soccer Clubs
